Arraignment of an accused consists of calling upon him by name, reading to him the charges in the arrest documents, demanding of him whether he pleads guilty or not guilty or, in misdemeanors, nolo contendere, and entering his plea. This hearing may be combined with right to counsel hearing. 

Source: [VA Circuit Court Criminal Glossary](http://www.courts.state.va.us/courts/circuit/resources/manuals/cc_manual_criminal/glossary.pdf)